    "text": "If the no-signaling-preserving Null-Boundary Response framework is applied to design incentives that prevent any statistical correlation between current reward signals and future quality scores in the Beagle imputation validation pipeline, then the imputation quality metric will behave as a martingale; this is falsified if a Granger causality test detects a significant predictive relationship from past incentive allocations to future quality.",
    "topic": "Incentive design with no-signaling constraint in genomics pipelines"
  },
  {
    "text": "A trillion-parameter Ling and Ring agent, when fine-tuned solely on Beagle imputation outputs without explicit causal genotype-to-phenotype priors, will achieve a Pearson correlation coefficient r ≤ 0.5 between its predicted imputation accuracy and the empirical validation accuracy from the Terra pipelines, falsifying the hypothesis that raw scale obviates the need for domain-specific causal structure in genomic imputation quality prediction.",
    "topic": "Scaled AI for imputation accuracy prediction vs causal modeling"
  }
